<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-09T11:14:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-09T11:14:00-05:00" n="426" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.01/12: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-09T11:00:00-05:14">September 9, 1930—11
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:45 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>25. Ecuadorean Government has decided to give full recognition to
                            existing Governments of Bolivia and Peru and sent yesterday telegraphic
                            instructions to this effect to its mission in La Paz and a note to
                            Peruvian Minister in Quito.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>